There’s not really any point to this outburst. I just needed to write it down. He is starting to ‘calm down’ and is less aggressive and our relationship is better than ever but I am so scared for him going back to a mainstream school.

We’re almost at the point where he can go back to school with additional support in place but never in a million years would you look at him or speak with him and think he may have any learning disability.

He has an appointment to see the psychologist soon who will take all of the evidence and hopefully make a formal diagnosis but we have now gone from ‘he probably has ADHD’ to ‘actually, he may have significant underdevelopment in his brain’

Today I got the report from the educational psychologist. He is scoring low - below average in all areas showing a substantial cognitive impairment. Which may be because of something physical or genetic factors rather than him just being ‘that awful kid’.

…he plays piano and guitar, can read music and is a black belt in karate. But put him in a classroom setting and all he’ll breaks loose. This spilled over into home life and last year (on my 40th birthday) he moved out of my house to live with his dad.

He’s been assessed by SALT, educational psychologists, Early Help teams, CAHMS and the youth justice service. ADHD and ASD have been questioned. Everyone who has met him has told me how he’s polite, engaging, intelligent, charming and curious. And he is…

Most people know of the problems we’ve been through with my son (14) in the last couple of years. Aggression, trouble with police, kicked out of school and eventually taken out of school by us to investigate what the hell has been going on…
